
This is the Perl distribution Term-Shell-Enhanced.

## Installation

Term-Shell-Enhanced installation is straightforward.
If your CPAN shell is set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Term::Shell::Enhanced

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

## Documentation

Term-Shell-Enhanced documentation is available as in POD.
So you can do:

    % perldoc Term::Shell::Enhanced

to read the documentation with your favorite pager.
